\[OP^2 = OE^2 + EF^2 - 2 \cdot OE \cdot EF \cdot \cos \angle EOP.\]Since $OPEF$ is a rhombus, $\angle EOP = \angle EOF = 60^\circ,$ so
\[OP^2 = OE^2 + EF^2 - OE \cdot EF.\]Also, $OE = x - 46,$ so
\[OP^2 = (x - 46)^2 + (92 - 2x)^2 - (x - 46)(92 - 2x).\]We want to minimize $x,$ subject to the constraint that $OP = OE = OF$ is a positive real number.  Thus, we want to minimize $x$ subject to the constraint that
