Let $F,$ $G,$ $H,$ $I,$ and $J$ be the points of tangency of the inscribed circle with sides $AB,$ $BC,$ $CD,$ $DE,$ and $EA,$ respectively.  Then
\[AF = AJ = 5 - r,\]so $FJ = 7 - 2r.$  Similarly, $BG = BF = 6 - r,$ so $FG = 5 - r.$

Since $\angle AFB = 180^\circ - \angle CDE,$
\[\cos \angle AFB = -\cos \angle CDE.\]Then
\[\frac{(6 - r)^2 + (5 - r)^2 - 7^2}{2 \cdot (6 - r) \cdot (5 - r)} = -\frac{(6 - r)^2 + 6^2 - (5 - r)^2}{2 \cdot (6 - r) \cdot 6}.\]This simplifies to $r = \frac{29}{15}.$

